"title": "5205: alliance",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5205: alliance",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The coalition of two or more parties in order to achieve a particular aim. Political alliances might be formalised in a treaty or sealed by marriage. Human rebellion against God is demonstrated in hostile alliances against his people culminating in the rejection of Christ and the final gathering and overthrow of the nations outside Jerusalem. Because God's people are to depend on him alone, unholy alliances are condemned; however God does work in partnership with human allies and encourages his people to work together.</p>\n<h2>Political alliances</h2>\n<h3>General examples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:1-Gen14:3\">GEN 14:1–14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen14:13\">GEN 14:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam27:2\">1SA 27:2</a></p>\n<h3>Alliances formalised in a treaty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:27\">GEN 21:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:31\">GEN 26:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:12\">1KI 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:19\">1KI 15:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr16:3\">2CH 16:3</a></p>\n<h3>Alliances sealed by marriage</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:1\">1KI 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:1\">2CH 18:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:6\">DAN 11:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:17\">DAN 11:17</a></p>\n<h2>Alliances against God and his people</h2>\n<h3>Surrounding nations against God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps83:5-Ps83:8\">PSA 83:5–83:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:5-Josh10:6\">JOS 10:5–10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:4-Josh11:5\">JOS 11:4–11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:1\">2CH 20:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:1-Isa7:2\">ISA 7:1–7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:8\">NEH 4:8</a></p>\n<h3>The nations against Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:25-Acts4:27\">ACT 4:25–4:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:1-Ps2:2\">PSA 2:1–2:2</a></p>\n<h3>The nations against Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:2\">ZEC 14:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:8-Rev20:9\">REV 20:8–20:9</a></p>\n<h3>The wicked against the righteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:13\">PSA 31:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:6\">PSA 56:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:3\">PSA 59:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:10\">PSA 71:10</a></p>\n<h3>The rich and powerful against the weak</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:3\">MIC 7:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:20-Ps94:21\">PSA 94:20–94:21</a></p>\n<h3>God is greater than human alliances</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps48:4-Ps48:5\">PSA 48:4–48:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:12\">NAM 1:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:22\">2CH 20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:4\">ISA 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek30:6\">EZK 30:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek31:17\">EZK 31:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Obad1:7\">OBA 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:8-Nah3:10\">NAM 3:8–3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Unholy alliances condemned by God</h2>\n<h3>God's people forbidden to ally with the unrighteous</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12\">EXO 34:12</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14-2Cor6:16\">2CO 6:14–6:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:6\">DEU 23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:7\">JOS 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:12\">JOS 23:12</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of alliances condemned by God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:7\">2KI 16:7</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:16\">2CH 28:16</a> <em>Ahaz's proposed alliance with Assyria</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:35-2Chr20:37\">2CH 20:35–20:37</a> <em>Jehoshaphat's alliance with Ahaziah of Israel</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1\">ISA 30:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:1\">HOS 12:1</a> <em>Israel's vacillation between Egypt and Assyria</em></p>\n<h3>The futility of trust in human allies</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:3\">ISA 31:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:21\">JER 13:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:20-Jer22:21\">JER 22:20–22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:19\">LAM 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>God works with human allies</h2>\n<h3>God uses Cyrus to deliver Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:14\">ISA 48:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:4\">ISA 13:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:2\">ISA 41:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:9\">JER 50:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:20-Jer51:23\">JER 51:20–51:23</a></p>\n<h3>Fellow-workers with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1\">2CO 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:9\">1CO 3:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:20</a></p>\n<h2>Believers allied in God's service</h2>\n<h3>Working together</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra5:2\">EZR 5:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:6\">NEH 4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:10\">1CO 15:10</a></p>\n<h3>Paul's fellow-workers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:3\">PHP 4:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:3\">ROM 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:21\">ROM 16:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor8:23\">2CO 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:25\">PHP 2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:24\">PHM 1:24</a></p>",
